HEADWORD: Diphyodont
<hw>Diph"y*o*dont</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ double
(<grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ to produce) +
<grk>'odoy`s</grk>, <grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, tooth.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having two successive sets of teeth (deciduous
and permanent), one succeeding the other; <as>as, a <ex>diphyodont</ex>
mammal; <ex>diphyodont</ex> dentition</as>; -- opposed to
<contr>monophyodont</contr>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An animal
having two successive sets of teeth.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diphyozooid</ent>⟦br⟧
